trans-unit.source: IntelliCode saves you time by putting what you're most likely to use at the top of your completion list.
trans-unit.target: IntelliCode saves you time by putting what you're most likely to use at the top of your completion list.

trans-unit.source: IntelliCode recommendations are based on thousands of open source projects on GitHub each with over 100 stars.
trans-unit.target: IntelliCode recommendations are based on thousands of open source projects on GitHub each with over 100 stars.

trans-unit.source: When combined with the context of your code, the completion list is tailored to promote common practices.
trans-unit.target: When combined with the context of your code, the completion list is tailored to promote common practices.

trans-unit.source: IntelliCode isn’t limited to statement completion.
trans-unit.target: IntelliCode isn’t limited to statement completion.

trans-unit.source: Signature help also recommends the most likely overload for your context.
trans-unit.target: Signature help also recommends the most likely overload for your context.

trans-unit.source: Recommendations for your types, based on your code (C#)
trans-unit.target: Recommendations for your types, based on your code (C#)

trans-unit.source: With this preview release, if you’re using C#, you can have IntelliCode learn patterns from your code, so it can make recommendations for types that aren’t in the open source domain, such as your own utility classes or domain specific library calls.
trans-unit.target: With this preview release, if you’re using C#, you can have IntelliCode learn patterns from your code, so it can make recommendations for types that aren’t in the open source domain, such as your own utility classes or domain specific library calls.

trans-unit.source: Inferring code style and formatting conventions
trans-unit.target: Inferring code style and formatting conventions

trans-unit.source: Keep your code consistent easily with Visual Studio IntelliCode, which dynamically creates an .editorconfig file from your codebase to define coding styles and formats.
trans-unit.target: Keep your code consistent easily with Visual Studio IntelliCode, which dynamically creates an .editorconfig file from your codebase to define coding styles and formats.

trans-unit.source: Recommendations for Controls and properties
trans-unit.target: Recommendations for Controls and properties

trans-unit.source: When typing XAML, IntelliCode will recommend the Control you are most likely to use in that context.
trans-unit.target: When typing XAML, IntelliCode will recommend the Control you are most likely to use in that context.

trans-unit.source: Additionally, within the context of a control, it will recommend the properties you are most likely to use, in the order in which you would have used them!
